                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-25T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 25, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 25—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. The following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 23, noon.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Vice Consul <persName corresp="#p_TK1">Takigawa</persName> stated
                                that yesterday Japanese troops after one hour’s fighting with old
                                Kirin troops near Imienpo caused them to retreat and that early this
                                morning 3,000 brigands attacked <pb facs="0827" n="723"
                                    xml:id="pg_723"/> the town and occupied the Chinese Eastern
                                Railway station at Sanchaho, 102 kilometers south of Harbin, thus
                                holding up traffic for a few hours.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Traffic on eastern line still suspended. Soviet management has
                                promised to furnish necessary rolling stock for transportation of
                                Japanese troops.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
